    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-23T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-23T06:00:00-05:00" n="400"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 ACI/10: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The American Representative to the French Committee of
                        National Liberation at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-23T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 23, 1943—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received November 24—7:13
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. From Murphy. Department’s 2097, November 9, 8 p.m. Massigli has now handed me
                    a communication acknowledging tripartite invitation to French Committee of
                    National Liberation to designate a French representative to Advisory Council for
                    Italy. Communication adds that this acceptance must not be considered as
                    committing the French Committee on the Italian question in its ensemble and more
                    particularly with respect to Government of Marshal Badoglio.</p>
                <p>The communication states that French representative to the Council <pb
                        facs="0443" n="431" xml:id="pg_431"/> will be designated shortly. If the
                    Council meets before such designation Massigli has been authorized to represent
                    the Committee.</p>
                <p>Sent to Department, repeated to London. [Murphy.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
